  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nepal Earthquake Relief Assistance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The devastating earthquake of 7.8 magnitude left more than 8,600 people dead. Additionally 488,789 houses were totally destroyed and 267,477 partially damaged. Millions of people were affected and left vulnerable due to the earthquake, resulting in a 20% increase in poverty.

The goal of this project is to reduce poverty of the communities through empowerment, livelihood programs and health promotion within the vicinities of Kaski and Nawalparasi districts. The objective of community empowerment and livelihood improvement is achieved through establishment and mobilization of Self-Help Groups (SHGs), introducing saving and credit schemes through the SHGs, adult literacy, sensitization on basic rights, mobilization of revolving funds, providing vocational and agricultural training, and developing small business. Similarly, the objective of health promotion is achieved through raising awareness on health, support and advocacy, conducting women/children&apos;s health camps, and WASH activities. Local organizations are also empowered through engaging them in disaster preparedness and response, and providing care and support to people living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA).</narrative>
  </description>
